subsection_content:
When the human papillomavirus (HPV) enters the skin bite, it causes infection and warts form. The virus spreads from person to person or from different parts of the body through:
Direct contact with warts.; Sharing personal hygiene items such as towels, razors, etc.; Having unsafe sex with someone infected with warts (genital warts); Biting your nails and picking at your cuticles; Shave.
